21 Hours Ago Giving an update on his Facebook page on Tuesday, Sowore said he would be returning to the CIID office “to pursue the struggle to get Marshal Abubakar freed from illegal and unjust imprisonment.” He said, “Yesterday (Monday), I visited the Criminal Investigation and Intelligence Bureau (CIID) at the FCT Command of the Nigeria Police Force, a place notoriously known as “Abattoir” where the brutal former SARS unit was domiciled. Upon arrival with supporters, the policemen descended on us, arrested and brutalised a number of our comrades claiming we came to attack the unit. “While waiting in their premises, a police lawyer also brought some papers he claimed were “cyberstalking charges,” it was riddled with errors and had just been hurriedly filed at the registry of the Federal High Court in Abuja, the charges did not include any of the initial allegations of “criminal defamation” as earlier adduced by the police when they arrested me in front of the Court of Appeal. “Several hours after I presented myself voluntarily to counter the lie that I “jumped bail,” they released me to my lawyers after they issued them bail papers. They never disputed the fact that I gave them my contact number and that they never tried to reach me before they swooped on my lawyer, Marshal Abubakar, illegally arrested and threw him into prison. Just to do the bidding of a so-called criminal Billionaire, Ned Nwoko.



